==English==
===Etymology===
From '''[[Sodom]]''', where the [[Bible]], in Genesis chapters 18 and 19 and elsewhere, suggests such a practice took place (see [[sodomite#Usage notes|the Usage Notes for "sodomite"]]).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
{{wikipedia}}
# [[immorality]] in general
# any of various forms of [[sexual]] [[intercourse]] held to be [[unnatural]], particularly [[bestiality]].
# [[anal sex]]
# {{rfv-sense}} {{archaic}} [[inhospitality]]

====Synonyms====
*(''bestiality''): [[bestiality]], [[zoophilia]]
*(''anal sex''): [[anal sex]], [[buggery]]

